commit_list.message: Show openvoice user the state 'recipient busy' when a recipient for an outgoing call is busy

Updating tests to use new updated connfu-gem naming

* Now using call jids rather than ids
* updated the stub names of presence and iqs that have changed

When a recipient doesn't answer an outgoing call from an openvoice user set the call as timed out.

* Will ensure the openvoice endpoint is correctly hangup
* Tested using sip2sip.info account as they allowed to change the timeout setting

Play on hold music when call is being transferred.

We are now using the lower level of commands and waiting so best to not try and overcomplicate the existing DSL helper methods.  This way we can refactor out common behaviour into the DSL gem from this implementation with out falling prey to premature extraction.

Use transfer_using_join rather than transfer

Will only transfer to the first endpoint for now
A user should be able to login into their account
Use Factory girl to create or build accounts
Sign up error messages should be shown to the user
Add some titles to the app and pages.
The input fields for passwords should of type password
When missing attributes are supplied we should better direct the user back to the sign up page
When running rake it should run the specs not try to run the default test task
Ignore rvmrc from git
Ensure rails app can talk to heroku redis addon
Use heroku redis and EC2 prism server
WIP continued to get recording and answering of an outbound call

Have changed the default to use our deployed version of the application. Also populating the missing fields with values that won't break the views on ebb-when

Easily add iptable rules from application puppet manifests.

Whenever defining an iptables rule from an application we must require the pre and post iptables files to be created otherwise rules are created on a blank server incorrectly. I couldn't find another way that worked to correctly ensure the order of loading the iptables rules.

Using an existing puppet module to handle iptable definition, checking and reloading[1]. Better creates the iptable rules using the name from puppet as a comment.

[1] http://bob.sh/puppet-iptables
On ubuntu mongodb was not being setup.
Released version 1.0.7
Released version 1.0.4
Bumping version

Update mongodb to version 1.8.1 so that we can enable journaling which should allow safe backups

Had to change apt source as 10gen is no longer supported the previous one. Also package name was changed so that a real version number could be used rather than a timestamp.
When setting hostname need to add to hosts file so that it can resolve
Apache site template set up on Ubuntu
Servers installing Munin failed due to missing folders.

Applications must allow commands to be ran as sudo for a group.

Puppet application configs can now call sudo::allow_command(group, command) to allow sudo access of a command. It will grant access to that command without requiring a password.

commit_list.message: Be able to define behaviour when a recipient of a dial is busy
Define behaviour for time out of a dial
We need to create call behaviour for outgoing calls being answered/ringing/etc without sending a dial command in the dsl

Ask for DTMF input with a prompt.

The ask command sent to prism currently only sets DTMF as the mode and has # has the terminator.

WIP Dial a single number.

Currently requires few more tests therefore in a branch. When running Rake the test connection handlers for the functional test calling a single number fails.
For consistency ensure there are functional tests for the recording dsl syntax.

Start and stop recording audio from a call.

Currently records a file to the filesystem fine but we have an error when sending the stop command to Prism.

Setting a http uri as the 'record_to' doesn't work also, Prism doesn't post the data to that URL.

Refactor out commands into their own files with relevant spec file.

Found it hard to manage a single file and test file for the many commands we now support.

Rather than use 'extensions/all' and require_relative just ensure the directory 'spec' is in the load path.

This was introduced in a previous commit[1] to allow running of individual tests.

To get tests working correctly in Rubymine we must add the 'spec' directory to the load path for the project settings. RubyMine -> Preferences... -> (Under project) Project Structure -> Load Path -> Add the directory spec

[1] https://github.com/zlu/play/commit/614b4625546316b5cb64b822181f758511c882a3

Iq parser could be better broken up so that the behaviour belonging to events and ozone is separate.

Moved ozone specific functionality to a separate parser and have the processing of events under an event processor.

No tests were removed, all correctly re-factored.

There is now a clear distinction between ozone specification and what happens to Connfu::Events. This will help if the underlying ozone implement was to be replaced.

We are using Component and Command too much.

Have tried to keep DSL specific language methods under dsl. This way we can keep testing the dsl under dsl_spec which deals with commands and potentially components in the future
Call handler used for continuation behavior was confusing as we use call handler terminology for the code being ran as a dial plan (the developer dsl)
Removed redundant parsing stub in connfu_spec as the containing specs don't require it
Call Handler (used for continuation) does not need to handle anything, only continue the call continuation
Removing unrequired debug lines
Change logger so that we don't see debug lines when running the tests
clean up spec_helper, removed irrelevant tests within iq_parser_spec

Cleared out all old style code and relevant tests to acheive passing state that can be better worked on.

We also wrote some tests around that were missing on the commands and current dsl implemented.
Relax gemspec requirement of rspec version
Fix broken test on Call Handler spec. We no longer require the event to be passed to #handle
say_complete event should resume programm executation and result iq should not
An answer command should not wait
Fixed failing spec because say commands require a from address
